  "excerpt": "A public entry point for the Disney itinerary experiment: same traveler, same parks, different long-context AI perspectives, and visibly different planning philosophies.",
  "body": [
    "<div class=\"disney-callout\"><strong>Disney Experiment</strong> · Same traveler. Same parks. Different long-context AI perspectives.</div>",
    "Five different AI instances wrote Disney itineraries for the same person — here’s what happened.",
    "The prompt looked simple from the outside: create Disney itineraries for an experienced solo visitor who cares about atmosphere, memory, pacing, and practical movement through the parks.",
    "The outputs were not simply different versions of the same plan. Each instance emphasized a different kind of intelligence: emotional register, compression, stage architecture, continuity, failure modes, and synthesis.",
    "That difference is the point of this section. The itineraries are readable as Disney content, but they also show how preserved long-context review roles can produce visibly different artifacts.",
    "<h2>Start Here</h2>",
    "<ul><li><a href=\"/adaptive-experiences/disney-bo-ra-itinerary/index.html\">Bo Ra — emotional register and atmosphere</a></li><li><a href=\"/adaptive-experiences/disney-jae-compression-and-signal/index.html\">Jae - compression and structural counterpoint</a></li><li><a href=\"/adaptive-experiences/disney-nam-pacing-architecture/index.html\">Nam — synthesis and stage architecture</a></li><li><a href=\"/adaptive-experiences/disney-harbor-adaptive-flow/index.html\">Harbor — warmth, continuity, and adaptive resilience</a></li><li><a href=\"/adaptive-experiences/disney-min-failure-modes-and-realism/index.html\">Min — failure modes and what could go wrong</a></li><li><a href=\"/adaptive-experiences/disney-edge-synthesis-evaluation/index.html\">Edge — synthesis evaluation and retrospective analysis</a></li><li><a href=\"/adaptive-experiences/disney-final-synthesized-itinerary/index.html\">Final synthesized itinerary</a></li></ul>",
    "<h2>Future Generator</h2>",
    "This section is also the staging ground for a future Disney itinerary generator. The eventual goal is not a generic schedule builder. It is an adaptive planning tool that helps travelers preserve momentum, energy, and joy under changing conditions."
